# BrainTwin — Cursor IDE Rules

## Project Overview
BrainTwin is a personal knowledge twin agent that captures everything the user consumes digitally (via Chrome extension + Telegram bot), processes it through an LLM enrichment pipeline, stores it in ChromaDB + SQLite, and enables a RAG-powered agent that competes against the user in knowledge battles.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3.11+ with FastAPI backend
- ChromaDB for vector search
- SQLite for structured data
- Claude API (Anthropic) for LLM enrichment and agent reasoning
- sentence-transformers for local embeddings
- Chrome Extension (Manifest V3) for browser content capture
- python-telegram-bot for mobile capture

## Code Style
- Use type hints everywhere
- Use async/await for all I/O operations
- Use pydantic models for data validation
- Keep functions small and focused
- Write docstrings for all public functions
- Use the `rich` library for CLI output/logging

## Architecture
- `/backend/capture/` — Content capture and extraction
- `/backend/knowledge/` — Storage, enrichment, embeddings
- `/backend/agent/` — RAG retrieval and LLM reasoning
- `/backend/competition/` — Game logic and scoring
- `/backend/telegram_bot/` — Mobile capture via Telegram
- `/extension/` — Chrome extension (JavaScript)

## Important Notes
- All data stays local (ChromaDB + SQLite in /data/)
- Use Claude Haiku for cheap enrichment tasks
- Use Claude Sonnet for agent reasoning (needs strong lateral thinking)
- Chrome extension talks to localhost:8000
- Skip sensitive sites (banking, email, login pages)
